social_posts.post_text:
Excited to announce that I have decided to partner with the Global Food Justice Alliance(GFJA) for this years #MyCauseMyCleats campaign. I chose to partner with this organization because they strive to combat malnutrition in food insecure populations while advocating for high quality foods produced through regenerative agriculture. 

Young children are particularly susceptible to the effects of micronutrient malnutrition. And while fruits and vegetables are great, the truth is that common nutrient deficiencies, like iron and B12, are best addressed through access to nutrient-dense food, especially meat.

From now through January 15th, every dollar donated to GFJA will purchase a @paleovalley 100% grass-fed meat stick (at cost) and send them to a food insecure child in the Cincinnati area. I will be donating $500 myself. 

Kids snacks are often high in sugar and unhealthy. Access to nutrient-dense foods, like these grass-fed meat snacks, can help make a difference in children's development and growth.

If you want to support this initiative and send nutrient-rich snacks to families in Ohio, donate today with the link in my bio!

https://www.globalfoodjustice.org/donations

Had a great time at the @nflpa annual rep meeting last week. Learned a lot, connected with some awesome members of our organization, and said “aloha” and “mahalo” more times than I can count..🤙🏽

Was an honor to back again for the 2nd annual @ajgloverfoundation 7on7 tournament last weekend!

The AJ Glover Foundation is a non-profit organization that has been able to make the most out of a tragic situation by pouring back into the community through supporting those in the Pediatric Intensive Care Unit at Children’s Nationwide Hospital and awarding scholarships to select seniors at all 3 of the Hilliard high schools. 

Was great to be able to contribute by being involved with an event like this!
